HEADWORD: Unsad
<hw>Un*sad"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>uns⟦ae⟧d</ets> unsated, insatiable. See <er>Un-</er> not, and
<er>Sad</er>.]</ety> <def>Unsteady; fickle.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, stormy people, <qex>unsad</qex> and ever untrue.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unsadden</ent>⟦br⟧
